# Project Structure & Development Workflow

This project follows specific patterns for development, testing, and deployment.

## Project Structure

### Root Directory for monorepo

```
betterware/
├── .cursor/commands/       # Cursor AI commands
├── .cursor/rules/          # Cursor AI rules
├── docs/                   # Documentation
├── packages/               # Monorepo packages
│   ├── mobile/             # React Native application for mobile
│   ├── shared/             # Shared project with utilities for "web" and "mobile" projects
│   └── web/                # ReactJs application for web
├── lerna.json              # Monorepo configuration using lerna
└── package.json            # Dependencies and scripts
```

### Root Directory for "web" application

```
packages/web/
├── public/                 # Static assets
├── src/                    # Source code (FSD architecture)
├── eslint.config.js        # ESLint configuration
├── index.html              # Main entry point for web application
├── package.json            # Dependencies and scripts
├── tsconfig.app.json       # Compiler options specific to main client-side application code
├── tsconfig.json           # Compiler options for TypeScript
├── tsconfig.node.json      # Covers the TypeScript settings for code that runs strictly in Node.js
└── vite.config.js          # Configuration file for Vite
```

### Root Directory for "mobile" application

```
packages/mobile/
├── android/                 # Fully functional Android Studio Gradle project
├── ios/                     # Native Apple Xcode project workspace
├── vendor/                  # Source code (FSD architecture)
├── .eslintrc.js             # ESLint configuration
├── .prettier.js             # Prettier configuration
├── .watchmanconfig          # Configuration for file-watching service used by Metro
├── app.json                 # The primary configuration file for React Native/Expo project
├── App.tsx                  # Main entry component for user interface
├── babel.config.js          # Pre-configured compiler rules to translate modern JavaScript/TypeScript syntax into code compatible with the underlying JavaScript engines
├── Gemfile                  # Ruby dependencies required for your iOS development environment
├── index.js                 # Entry point for the entire application
├── jest.config.js           # How Jest runs and compiles unit and component tests
├── metro.config.js          # Configuration file for the Metro Bundler
├── package.json             # Project metadata, third-party dependencies, and automated execution scripts
└── tsconfig.json            # Configuration settings for React Native CLI apps that leverage TypeScript
```

### Source Code Organization for both "web" and "mobile" applications

```
src/
├── app/                    # Application initialization + FSD app layer
├── entities/               # Business objects (nouns)
│   └── [entity]/api/       # API operations
├── features/               # User interactions (verbs)
│   └── [feature]/api/      # API operations
├── shared/                 # Reusable utilities
│   ├── api/                # API clients
│   ├── lib/                # Utilities
│   ├── ui/                 # UI components
│   └── constants/          # Constants
├── widgets/                # Large UI blocks
├── App.tsx                 # Home Page
└── index.css               # Global styles
```

## Development Scripts

### Available Commands from root directory

```bash
# Development
npm run build                  # Everything that can build
npm run build:shared           # Shared library only
npm run web                    # Start development server with Turbopack
npm run start:mobile           # Start the Metro bundler
npm run ios / android          # Native app on device/simulator

# Code Quality
npm run lint                   # Run lint on projects
npm run test                   # Unit testing
```

### Package Manager

- **Package Manager**: npm 11.6.1
- **Node Version**: Configured via `.nvmrc` (if present)
- **Lock File**: `package-lock.lock`

