### TypeScript Configuration

```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "ES2017",
    "lib": ["dom", "dom.iterable", "esnext"],
    "strict": false,
    "moduleResolution": "bundler",
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["./src/*"]
    }
  }
}
```

**Note:** This project currently has `strict: false`. Prefer explicit types and avoid `any`; consider enabling `strict: true` for new modules.

## Logging & Error Tracking

### Centralized Error Utilities

The project includes comprehensive error tracking and logging utilities in `src/shared/lib/errorTracking.ts`:

```typescript
// ✅ Import error tracking utilities
import {
  trackError, // Track errors to external services
  getErrorMessage, // Safely extract error messages
  normalizeError, // Convert unknown errors to Error objects
  logDev, // Development-only logging
  warnDev, // Development-only warnings
  errorDev, // Development-only errors
  trackEvent, // Track events for analytics
} from "@/shared/lib";

// ✅ Error handling pattern
try {
  await riskyOperation();
} catch (error) {
  const errorObj = normalizeError(error);
  trackError(errorObj, {
    feature: "auth",
    action: "login",
    userId: user?.id,
  });
  throw errorObj;
}

// ✅ Development logging (automatically removed in production)
logDev("User authenticated successfully", { userId: user.id });
warnDev("Token expires in 5 minutes", { expiresAt: tokenExpiry });
errorDev("Authentication failed", { error: error.message });

// ✅ Event tracking for analytics
trackEvent("user_login", {
  method: "msal",
  timestamp: Date.now(),
  userId: user.id,
});
```

### Retry Logic

Use the retry utility with exponential backoff for resilient operations:

```typescript
import { retryWithBackoff } from "@/shared/lib";

// ✅ Retry with exponential backoff
const result = await retryWithBackoff(
  async () => await syncTokenToServer(token),
  {
    maxAttempts: 3,
    initialDelayMs: 1000,
    maxDelayMs: 8000,
    onRetry: (attempt, error) => {
      logDev(`Retry attempt ${attempt}/3`, { error: error.message });
    },
  },
);
```

### Error Context Guidelines

Always provide meaningful context when tracking errors:

```typescript
// ✅ Good: Rich context for debugging
trackError(error, {
  feature: "auth",
  action: "token-refresh",
  userId: user?.id,
  tokenExpiry: token?.exp,
  retryAttempt: attempt,
});

// ❌ Poor: Minimal context
trackError(error);
```

